Rabies, human, vaccine allergies: RFI 971120182940
Date: Fri, 21 Nov 1997 09:46:02 +0100
From: yrotivel@pasteur.fr (yolande ROTIVEL)

I have no information nor experience on the possible role of interferon in
allergic reactions to serum and vaccine against rabies. But serum alone
(especially ERIG) is responsible for allergic reactions (Quincke edema,
urticaria, serum sickness...). I have seen too, urticaria in patients given
Suckling Mouse Brain vaccine, especially after several repeated doses of the
vaccine. In the case of your patient, the best way would be to use a cell
culture vaccine (Verorab, or PCEC) and HRIG, if available. Otherwise, I
would give him the full PET as usual, but with antihistamine drugs, and test
his rabies antibody titer, [to avoid giving him too many repeated injections.
--
Yolande Rotivel, M.D.
Chief of the Rabies Treatment Center
Deputy Director of the National Reference Center for Rabies
